<h2>Types of deeds you will find in an online EC TN record</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    When reviewing your online EC TN results, each entry represents a registered deed. The most common deed types you will encounter are: Sale Deed (Kiraiya Pattiram in Tamil) which records a property transfer between a buyer and seller; Mortgage Deed (Adhanam or Adhu Pattiram) which records a property pledged as security for a loan; Release Deed (Vithuvidai Pattiram) which records the cancellation of a previous mortgage; Partition Deed which records the legal division of jointly-owned property among co-owners; Gift Deed (Varadhanam) which records the voluntary transfer of property as a gift without consideration; and Power of Attorney which records authorization given to a third party to act on behalf of the owner.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    Each deed listed in the online EC TN record includes an Index Number which is the unique registration reference. The index number follows the format: Book Number / Part Number / Volume Number / Year. If a deed shows a mortgage and a subsequent release, the property is clear of that specific charge. If a mortgage appears without a corresponding release deed, the mortgage is still active and the property carries that encumbrance. Buyers must always check both the mortgage entries and the corresponding release entries carefully. For verification guidance, consult the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> resource library.
</p>

