<h2>How to search EC Villangam online on TNreginet</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    To view your Villangam details, visit the official registration portal at tnreginet.gov.in. Under the main menu, navigate to "E-Services", click on "Encumbrance Certificate", and select "View EC". You will be presented with a search form where you can search by survey number or document number.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    For a survey number search, select your zone, district, sub-registrar office (SRO), and the revenue village from the respective dropdowns. Next, enter the main survey number and sub-division number in the designated boxes. Choose the start date and end date for the search window, enter the verification code, and press the Search button. The system will display the transaction table instantly, showing Book I entries. If you need a certified copy with an official digital signature, you must log in, complete the application form, pay the search and copy fees, and wait for SRO approval. For portal walkthroughs, review our <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> SRO guide.
</p>

