<h2>Verifying property title with Patta, Chitta, and Villangam EC</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    A complete title search in Tamil Nadu requires cross-verifying multiple documents. The three pillars of land verification are Patta (ownership record), Chitta (village register showing extents), and the Villangam EC (transaction record). When you perform an <strong>ec villangam online</strong> search, you get the list of all registered transactions. However, you must match this list against the revenue records.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    For instance, if a sale deed is registered in the EC, but the Patta transfer (mutation) was never completed, the revenue records will still show the old owner name. This mismatch can cause loan rejections or legal disputes during future sales. Similarly, verifying Chitta ensures that the land extent and survey boundaries listed in your sale deed match the physical maps maintained by the Village Administrative Officer (VAO). Prospective buyers must ensure that the name on the Patta, the land details in the Chitta, and the transaction details in the EC are fully consistent. If you need details on other states, consult the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> comparison dashboard.
</p>

