<h2>Why pre-1987 Villangam EC records are not online in Tamil Nadu</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    While the TNreginet portal has successfully digitised registration records for the last few decades, users seeking older data will find that pre-1987 records are not available online. The state registration department started computerising transaction details from 1987. For any transaction registered prior to this year, the entries are recorded in large physical ledgers called Book I and Index II registers.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    To search for a Villangam EC for years prior to 1987, you must visit the respective Sub-Registrar Office in person or hire a document writer. You will need to submit a manual application form detailing the property survey numbers, boundaries, taluk name, and revenue village name. A clerk will manually search the physical ledgers page-by-page to trace the title history and prepare a handwritten or certificate copy. This manual process takes longer, typically between seven to fifteen working days, and requires paying search fees and copying fees manually at the treasury counter.
</p>

