<h2>Using certified EC as a legal document in Puducherry</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    A certified EC containing the digital signature of the Puducherry Sub-Registrar is legally valid and admissible in courts under the Indian Evidence Act. It is required for registering mortgages, processing bank loans, and resolving civil title disputes. The unsigned search copy is not legally valid and cannot be submitted to banks or government departments.
</p>

<h2>Bilingual glossary of Puducherry property registration terms</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    Understanding local terms is essential for interpreting land records. We have prepared a glossary explaining terms for the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> search:
</p>
<ul class="guide-list" style="margin-left: 2rem; color: #475569; line-height: 1.8;">
    <li><strong>Commune</strong>: Local administrative division grouping several revenue villages.</li>
    <li><strong>SRO</strong>: Sub-Registrar Office where deeds are formally registered.</li>
    <li><strong>Patta</strong>: Revenue document proving land ownership.</li>
    <li><strong>Chitta</strong>: Village field book showing landowner and area extents.</li>
    <li><strong>Form 15</strong>: EC listing property transactions.</li>
    <li><strong>Form 16</strong>: Nil Encumbrance Certificate.</li>
    <li><strong>Mutation</strong>: Process of transferring owner name in revenue records.</li>
</ul>
<p class="content-text">
    Always check at least 30 years of history. Banks and legal advisors require this to ensure no old mortgages remain active. For state-specific instructions, visit our main <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> homepage for comparisons.
</p>

<h2>Difference between Form 15 and Form 16 in Puducherry</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    When you apply for an EC on the Puducherry Registration Portal, the output document is generated in one of two formats based on the historical entries found. If the property has undergone transactions like sales, gifts, partitions, or active mortgages during the search period, the SRO will issue a Form 15. This form contains a table detailing the date of transaction, the names of the executing parties, the document number, book number, and the total sale value or mortgage amount. It provides a complete history of the title chain.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    Conversely, if no transactions are recorded on the property during the specified search period, the Sub-Registrar Office will issue a Form 16. This is commonly referred to as a Nil Encumbrance Certificate. It indicates that the property is free from any registered encumbrances or transactions for the queried years. Both forms are official legal records but serve different purposes in verifying title status.
</p>

<h2>How to check the status of your Puducherry EC application online</h2>
