<h2>What is an encumbrance check and why do you need it?</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    An encumbrance certificate is a transcript of transactions registered at the Sub-Registrar Office (SRO). Digitised systems allow citizens to perform this check online. In most states, running an <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> verify is the standard process to confirm that a property is free of financial liabilities.
</p>
