<h2>Cross-verifying mutation register (Khata/Patta) with EC check</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    A comprehensive property title check involves cross-verifying the EC with mutation records. The EC shows transaction history, but the mutation register shows owner details recognized by revenue authorities (e.g. Patta, Khata, or Bhoomi RTC).
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    Ensure that the seller name in the registered sale deed matches the latest entry in the revenue database. If there is a mismatch, a mutation has not been completed. This mismatch can lead to transaction rejections during future sales. Once verified, you can proceed to the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> status page to request your certified copy.
</p>

