<h2>What is an EC application and why do you need it?</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    An Encumbrance Certificate application is a formal request submitted to the Sub-Registrar Office asking for a search of all registered property transactions over a specified period. The resulting certificate lists every sale, mortgage, lease, gift, partition, or court attachment recorded against the property.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    Banks require this certificate before approving home loans. Courts require it during title disputes. Government departments require it for mutation and Patta transfer applications. Without a valid and current EC, most property transactions in India cannot legally proceed. Submitting your application through the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> portal is the fastest and most reliable way to obtain this certificate.
</p>

