<h2>Documents required to apply EC online in Tamil Nadu</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    No physical documents need to be uploaded when applying for EC through TNReginet. However, you must have the following information ready before beginning the application:
</p>
<ul class="guide-list" style="margin-left: 2rem; color: #475569; line-height: 1.8;">
    <li><strong>Sub-Registrar Office (SRO) Name</strong>: The SRO where the property was registered. Find this from the original sale deed or patta.</li>
    <li><strong>Village Name</strong>: The revenue village name as registered. Use the exact Tamil transliteration from the sale deed.</li>
    <li><strong>Survey Number</strong>: Main survey number of the land parcel. For plots, this is the parent survey from which the layout was formed.</li>
    <li><strong>Subdivision Number</strong>: The subdivision of the survey number, if any. Leave blank if searching at the main survey level.</li>
    <li><strong>Search Period</strong>: Start date and end date of the EC search. This determines how many years back the records are searched.</li>
    <li><strong>Registered Mobile Number and Email</strong>: Your TNReginet account credentials for OTP and notifications.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Step-by-step guide to apply EC online in Tamil Nadu</h2>
<ol class="guide-list" style="margin-left: 2rem; color: #475569; line-height: 1.8;">
    <li>Open tnreginet.gov.in in your browser.</li>
    <li>Click "User Registration" if you are new. Provide Aadhaar-linked mobile number and complete OTP verification to create your account.</li>
