    <li>From the top menu, click "E-Services" and select "Encumbrance Certificate".</li>
    <li>On the EC page, click "Apply for EC" (not "View EC" — that is the free preview without digital signature).</li>
    <li>Select your district from the dropdown. Then select the Sub-Registrar Office.</li>
    <li>Enter the village name. A suggestions list will appear — select the matching village exactly as registered.</li>
    <li>Enter the survey number and subdivision number.</li>
    <li>Set the "From Date" (start of search period) and "To Date" (today or the date the bank requires).</li>
    <li>Click "Search" to preview matching records.</li>
    <li>Review the preview. Confirm the property details match.</li>
    <li>Click "Apply" to proceed to the application form.</li>
    <li>Fill in the applicant details: Name, address, mobile number, purpose of EC.</li>
    <li>Review the fee calculation shown on screen. Confirm the amount.</li>
    <li>Proceed to online payment via Net Banking, UPI, or Debit Card.</li>
    <li>After successful payment, your application is submitted to the SRO officer for digital signing.</li>
    <li>Track status from "My Applications" in your TNReginet dashboard.</li>
    <li>Once approved, download the digitally signed EC PDF from your dashboard.</li>
</ol>

