<h2>Understanding Kaveri 2.0 portal for Bangalore property search</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    The Inspector General of Registration and Stamps in Karnataka introduced Kaveri 2.0 to replace the legacy Kaveri portal. The upgraded system provides a faster interface, secure user registration, and streamlined workflow for property registration and document searches. It uses Aadhaar-based authentication to verify the identity of applicants, reducing fraudulent searches and improving data security.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    Kaveri 2.0 categorizes services into pre-registration and post-registration options. The search and application for an encumbrance certificate falls under post-registration services. The database contains digitized records for properties in Bangalore spanning the past thirty years. For records older than thirty years, manual searches at the respective Sub-Registrar Office might still be necessary. The integrated <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> search feature of the portal allows citizens to verify records instantly before placing a formal application for a certified signed copy.
</p>

