<h2>Information required for Bangalore EC application</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    To ensure your application is processed without delay, you must collect accurate property details. Even a minor discrepancy in the survey number or village name can cause the application to be rejected by the SRO officer, requiring you to apply again. Refer to your original sale deed, parent deed, or partition deed to obtain these parameters:
</p>
<ul class="guide-list" style="margin-left: 2rem; color: #475569; line-height: 1.8;">
    <li><strong>SRO Office</strong>: Identify which specific Sub-Registrar Office in Bangalore holds your property records. Examples include Rajajinagar SRO, Bommanahalli SRO, Begur SRO, or Banaswadi SRO.</li>
    <li><strong>Revenue hobli and village</strong>: Hoblis are sub-divisions of taluks, and villages are specific administrative divisions. Check your property tax receipt or sale deed for this.</li>
    <li><strong>Property Measurement and Boundaries</strong>: East-to-west and north-to-south measurements, alongside adjacent property details (road, empty site, or specific house number).</li>
    <li><strong>Identification Numbers</strong>: Survey number, subdivision number, plot number, khata number, or PID number. For apartments, note down the specific flat number, block number, and floor number.</li>
    <li><strong>Search Period</strong>: Banks usually require a minimum of 13 years of history, while some older properties might require a full 30-year search to satisfy legal title checks. You can configure this easily using the online <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> search criteria.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to track and download certified Bangalore EC from Kaveri portal</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    After submitting your application and completing the payment on Kaveri 2.0, your request is routed to the corresponding Sub-Registrar Office. A designated clerk reviews the property records and generates the draft certificate. The Sub-Registrar then verifies the draft and applies their digital signature.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    To track the progress of your application, login to your Kaveri 2.0 account and go to the Saved Applications menu. The dashboard will show the status of your application. Once the status updates to Approved, a download link will become active. You can download the PDF containing the digital signature of the Sub-Registrar. This digital document is legally equivalent to a physical stamp copy under the Information Technology Act. The portal also allows you to check status using the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> application number.
</p>

