    The state of Tamil Nadu has integrated two key databases for property validation: the TNreginet portal run by the Registration Department, and the Anyal Patta Chitta portal managed by the Revenue Department. The registration system records deeds, transfers, mortgages, and release agreements, while the revenue system logs patta ownership and chitta land records.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    When you search the registration portal, the system searches the SRO registers. If there are registered transactions, they are compiled in Form 15, which lists buyers, sellers, deed numbers, and registration dates. If no deeds are registered during the selected years, the portal issues a Nil encumbrance certificate or Form 16. Searching through the official <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> platform guarantees that you get an authentic, verified document for legal and financial use.
</p>

<h2>Why verifying your TN land records online is critical</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    Buying agricultural land or housing plots in Tamil Nadu carries significant financial risk if the title history is not verified. An encumbrance certificate highlights transactions like sale deeds, lease deeds, partition deeds, and court-ordered attachments.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    Furthermore, banking institutions require a search record spanning thirteen to thirty years before approving land development or construction loans. Any unregistered transaction, incomplete chain, or outstanding mortgage in the SRO database can lead to application rejection. Using the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> search utilities allows buyers to identify these issues early and request necessary documents from the seller before signing agreements.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    In addition, verification helps buyers check if the land is subject to government acquisition or restricted under local development regulations. Agricultural lands, forest buffers, and coastal zones often have legal restrictions on sale. These details are updated in the registry records and will show up during the search. Verifying these records online safeguards your investment and ensures a clean title transaction.
</p>

