<h2>Importance of TNReginet EC in legal proceedings</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    Courts in Tamil Nadu frequently require an EC as supporting evidence in property-related disputes, succession cases, and partition suits. The encumbrance certificate from TNReginet is considered an official document and is admissible as evidence of registered transactions. In succession cases where a property is inherited, the EC helps identify any outstanding loans or encumbrances created by the deceased that may have to be settled by the legal heirs before a fresh registration is made.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
