<h2>Understanding the Difference: Statement of Encumbrance vs Nil EC</h2>
<p class="content-text">
    When you submit an online search, the output depends on whether transactions occurred. If there are registered deeds, the portal generates a Statement of Encumbrance, listing each transaction. If no transactions took place during the selected period, the portal generates a Nil Encumbrance Certificate.
</p>
<p class="content-text">
    While viewing online reports is quick, the output from the <strong><a href="https://econline.in/">ec online</a></strong> search screen is intended only for verification and does not have the legal status of a certified copy. For legal proceedings, you must submit a signed application through Meeseva centers or online portal to obtain a digitally signed certificate from the Sub-Registrar.
</p>

